select name+' ('+product+' '+cast(serverproperty('productversion') as nvarchar(800))+' '+
cast(serverproperty('productlevel') as nvarchar(800))+' '+cast(serverproperty('edition') as nvarchar(800))+' '+ provider+')' 
from sys.servers where server_id = 0

DECLARE @productVersion nvarchar(128)
SELECT @productVersion = CONVERT(nvarchar(128), SERVERPROPERTY('ProductVersion'))
DECLARE @majorVersion tinyint
SELECT @majorVersion = CONVERT(tinyint, SUBSTRING(@productVersion, 0, CHARINDEX('.' , @productVersion)))
DECLARE @serverLevel tinyint
SET @serverLevel = @majorVersion * 10
select @serverLevel

select name, COMPATIBILITY_LEVEL, collation_name, state_desc, user_access_desc, is_auto_shrink_on, recovery_model_desc
from sys.databases WHERE name='{0}'

    db.name AS [Database name],
    type_desc AS [File type],
    Physical_Name AS Location,
	Size*8/1024 as [Size MB],
	mf.state_desc as [File state],
	db.state_desc as [DB state]
FROM
    sys.master_files mf
INNER JOIN 
    sys.databases db ON db.database_id = mf.database_id
where db.name='{0}'

TextItems.Content:
SELECT df.name, 
	df.size/128.0 FileSizeInMB,
	df.size/128.0 - CAST(FILEPROPERTY(df.name, 'SpaceUsed') AS int)/128.0 AS EmptySpaceInMB,
	df.type_desc as [File type],
	df.state_desc as [State],
	df.physical_name as [Physical path]
FROM sys.master_files as df
	INNER JOIN sys.databases db ON
	df.database_id=db.database_id 
WHERE db.database_id>4
	AND df.state<>0
	ORDER BY df.Name, df.type_desc
